How to make a new msp project:\
\
1. Choose new project.\
2. Choose Carbon bundle.\
3. Pick name and location for your object\
4. Add frameworks from Project menu\
	a) MaxAPI.framework\
	b) MaxAudioAPI.framework\
5. Move them into the "External Frameworks" folder. (Carbon.framework should be in there too. already.)\
6. Move a .c file into your directory if you want and add to project. \
7. Move into "Sources" folder, where main.c should be residing. Consider deleting main.c\
8. Double click the target icon (lego block with green check mark) to open info dialog.\
9. Go to General, and click "Packaging". \
10. Change the setting of "Wrapper Extension" from "bundle" to "mxo" by clicking in the value field. \
11. Click "Search Paths"\
12. Click in value field of "Header Search Paths" and add (space-separated):\
../c74support/msp-includes ../c74support/max-includes\
assuming that's where those directories are. \
13. Nothing in Library Search Paths\
14. Click into Frameworks Search Paths and type:\
$(LOCAL_LIBRARY_DIR)/Frameworks\
15. Nothing in Rez search paths.\
16. Go to "Common Settings"\
17. Remove what's in Prefix Header, and replace with \
../c74support/max-includes/ext_carbon_prefix.h\
18. UNcheck "Precompile Prefix Header"\
19. Change type of product to iLaX instead of BNDL, and remove Identifier information.\
20. Make sure the right things are assigned to the target\
21. Remove Info.Plist, keeping InfoPlist.strings (might already be like this)\
22. Change Library Style to "Bundle"  (might not be needed)\
